 @simon6071  You don't seem to understand that the carbon footprint you're talking about is calculated by dividing the gross amount of pollution produced by a country divided by its population.  Qatar is an oil exporter, which means that the country does produce a lot of pollution, but all the oil it produces is exported to Europe, the US, China, etc.  Thus, Europeans, Americans, Chinese, Indians, etc are all indirectly responsible of the pollution produced by Qatar since Qatar produces the oil OTHER COUNTRIES consume.  Then, Qataris seem to pollute much more than other countries, but it's only because they produce oil consumed by other countries and also because their population is only of 2.6 million.

I'm not saying that Qatar and other oil producing countries aren't responsible of pollution, but they aren't responsible of the entire problems on the planet.  Remember that corporations produce what consumers buy.  Thus, all individuals are responsible for the pollution on our planet.

If the US, Europe, China, India and all other countries all reduced their oil imports, then oil producing countries would reduce their oil production and they would thus produce less pollution.

