 @Julia Donati  And I wish you wouldn't read the only 'approved' science on the issue as though it were your Bible. There are many scientists (prominent with PHDs from various prestigious universities) that have questions and problems with current climate models. Not YT conspiracy nuts (though plenty of those around), but real, empirical data founded scientists presenting tons of data explaining this global 'crisis' is unfounded. Are they the majority? No. Not that science is dictated by vote. Could they be way off base? Sure. Though they at least present their data with verifiable stats. 

My problem isn't with seeing a large consensus of scientists citing global warming over the last 100 years. Or their speculating what 'may' happen by models over the next 100 years. It is the silencing of scientists disputing those models (and some/many of the stats present and past). These guys show their data and make it available. It is usually the same data mainstream scientists used to make their claims. If they got it wrong, fine. Have the major climate crisis scientists show their mistakes. Problem is they don't. SERIOUSLY. They slander dissenters and never 'bother' to explain how they got it wrong or correct when others say they manipulated data. That isn't cool. Just sayn... 

The fact that nearly any mainstream media outlet worldwide or the social media giants will ever even 'present' this dissent (using any data points made or questions raised) is troubling, and begins to look more like activism then science.

